# Sanity

Schema: `slug` (unique), `order`, inline `seo`, PT `body`, image `alt`, parent `weak: false`

GROQ in `queries.ts` only: draft filter, explicit fields (no top-level `...`), `slug { current }`, `seo { title, description }`

DRY: one query per concern — fragments in `queries.ts`, access via `fetchers.ts` (`16-dry.mdc`).

## Cache & revalidation

- All `safeFetch` calls tag **`cms`** — authority: `lib/cache-tags.ts` (see `16-dry.mdc`)
- ISR fallback: `revalidate = 300` on public routes
- On-demand: Sanity webhook → `/api/revalidate` — skill: **`setup-revalidation`**
- Webhook filter, path map, new `_type` handling → this rule + `app/api/revalidate/route.ts`
- Secret query param & env → **`17-security.mdc`** (do not duplicate auth rules here)

```ts
const data = await safeFetch<T>(query, { slug }); if (!data) notFound()
```

Workflow: `add-sanity-query` → `add-fetcher` → route skills (`new-page` / `new-leaf-route`).
